<p>39) Download all files in a directory using WGET
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
To download all files in the directory using WGET in Linux, the following command can be used</p>

<p>wget -H -r ‚Äìlevel=1 -k -p http://www.tldp.org/HOWTO/Serial-Programming-HOWTO/</p>

<p>-r, ‚Äìrecursive
Specify recursive download.
-l, ‚Äìlevel=NUMBER
Maximum recursion depth (inf or 0 for infinite).
-k, ‚Äìconvert-links
Make links in downloaded HTML point to local files.
-p, ‚Äìpage-requisites
Get all images, etc. needed to display HTML page.</p>

